02:55.041 --> 02:56.275
Okay, tell us.

02:56.277 --> 02:58.143
[chase] so, with me doing all
the in-house manufacturing,

02:58.212 --> 03:01.213
This product last year was
$2,200 for me to make.

03:02.382 --> 03:03.481
What about that one?

03:03.484 --> 03:05.684
[chase] that tonneau cover cost
me $490.

03:06.753 --> 03:08.620
-[arlene] wow.
-75% margin.

03:09.823 --> 03:11.023
So where do you make these?

03:11.091 --> 03:13.025
I actually built my own
manufacturing facility

03:13.093 --> 03:14.259
In kelowna.

03:14.728 --> 03:15.960
-Oh, you did?
-[michele] no way.

03:16.030 --> 03:17.896
[chase] me and my parents,
we bought 30 acres together...

03:17.964 --> 03:19.898
-Yeah.
-...About nine years ago.

03:19.900 --> 03:22.234
My parents, obviously, the
majority of it.

03:22.302 --> 03:24.603
So we actually built a 4,500
square foot shop.

03:25.839 --> 03:28.307
Over time, I've been able to
acquire all the manufacturing

03:28.375 --> 03:30.776
Equipment to build every single
piece in-house.

03:32.379 --> 03:35.947
[vincenzo] is the property, is
it part of the deal?

03:36.016 --> 03:37.816
No, it is not.

03:38.818 --> 03:40.852
Chase, I'm dying to ask what
your sales are.

03:40.921 --> 03:45.156
In the last year, I by myself
built 200 units...

03:45.225 --> 03:46.391
Whoa.

03:46.459 --> 03:47.693
...Totally just over a million
dollars in sales last year.

03:48.561 --> 03:50.429
What are you projecting for next
year with this new product?

03:52.065 --> 03:55.600
