04:30.371 --> 04:33.171
I'm actually only 29 years old,
so the banks don't look at me

04:33.239 --> 04:35.974
With a lot of--you know, a lot
of security, so.

04:36.876 --> 04:38.577
And what's your background?

04:38.645 --> 04:40.312
You know, this sort of industry
has been my passion.

04:40.380 --> 04:42.380
I used to race professional
motocross.

04:42.449 --> 04:43.915
No way!

04:43.917 --> 04:45.817
[chase] and then I actually
bought a snowmobile.

04:46.520 --> 04:48.687
I had a bunch of problems with
it, so I fully redesigned

04:48.755 --> 04:51.456
The hood and found that if I
wanted to continue to design

04:51.458 --> 04:53.225
Stuff I have to get some of my
own equipment.

04:54.194 --> 04:57.362
I taught myself cad and all the
different design softwares to be

04:57.430 --> 04:58.530
Able to use it.

04:58.598 --> 04:59.731
-Good for you.
-Yeah.

04:59.800 --> 05:02.467
-Do you know what you've done?
-I like to think I do.

05:02.535 --> 05:03.869
You're so humble though.

05:03.937 --> 05:05.337
-You're really humble.
-Thank you.

05:05.939 --> 05:07.105
So, chase, who all helped you
come up with your valuation

05:07.173 --> 05:08.740
Of $6.6 million?

05:10.077 --> 05:11.743
That was through my accountant
and my family.

05:13.146 --> 05:15.747
So my parents, my mom and dad
are--they are involved

05:15.749 --> 05:16.648
In the company.

05:16.716 --> 05:19.050
My dad's actually the delivery
driver.

05:19.119 --> 05:20.318
-Okay.
-[michele laughs]

05:20.321 --> 05:22.120
[chase] and he drives trucks all
over.

05:22.188 --> 05:23.288
That's so cute.

05:23.357 --> 05:25.991
[chase] and then my mom,
she does all my accounting.

05:26.059 --> 05:28.360
Yeah, I think with where our
profit margins are,

05:28.428 --> 05:29.928
I definitely think it's
a fair valuation.

05:29.996 --> 05:31.830
So are your parents
investigators in the company

05:31.832 --> 05:32.864
Or do you pay them or--

05:32.933 --> 05:34.499
-No, they are not.
-They're just helping you out?

05:34.567 --> 05:36.401
-[chase] correct.
-Do they make a salary?

05:36.469 --> 05:39.371
My mom, I actually--I actually
bought her a new truck.

05:39.439 --> 05:40.505
-There you go.
-[manjit] okay.

05:40.574 --> 05:41.873
[chase] so that keeps her happy.

05:41.875 --> 05:45.677
And my dad last year for
christmas got a 1969 chevelle.

05:45.746 --> 05:46.878
[wes] there you go, good job.

05:46.947 --> 05:47.946
[manjit] this is a family
business.

05:48.014 --> 05:49.648
[arlene] so, chase, I'm gonna
make you an offer.

05:49.716 --> 05:51.583
I don't wanna take any equity.

05:51.651 --> 05:53.952
I would give you the million
dollars for a 10% royalty.

05:55.055 --> 05:57.989
And I'll do that until I get
three times my capital back.

05:58.057 --> 05:59.691
-And then I'm out.
-Thank you.

05:59.693 --> 06:01.293
I appreciate that.

06:03.229 --> 06:05.797
Chase, for me, it's not a
company yet.

06:06.332 --> 06:07.532
It's a single product.

06:07.600 --> 06:12.437
I wish you had more proof that
the tonneau cover is gonna be

06:12.505 --> 06:13.538
Something that the market is
looking for

06:13.606 --> 06:16.274
And that you have sales.

06:16.342 --> 06:17.509
I'm gonna be out.

06:19.346 --> 06:20.712
I'm not gonna make you an offer.

06:21.414 --> 06:26.184
One of the--one of the elements
in any business that sometimes

06:26.186 --> 06:32.424
